diff_analysis.evidence: The diff primarily removes various connection/updater providers and refactors configuration, logging, and model classes. New code additions (e.g., MongoIndex annotations, collection/index initialization, logging changes, stats representations, URL/path constant changes, and simplifications of map mappers) do not introduce direct handling of HTTP request parameters, HTML generation, SQL construction, deserialization of untrusted data, CSRF-relevant state changes, or authorization checks. No new dynamic query building or execution based on user input is present. Therefore, none of CWE-79, CWE-352, CWE-502, CWE-89, or CWE-862 are introduced by the NEW code.
